{
  "texts": [
    "Emerging applications also include the integration of wearable and augmented reality systems, where miniaturized odor generators and AI algorithms create interactive olfactory interfaces.",
    "These systems have potential uses in education, entertainment, and therapy, allowing users to experience enhanced sensory environments.",
    "For instance, wearable olfactory devices are in development to simulate realistic odors in virtual reality settings, providing immersive experiences in gaming or training simulations (Tewell and Ranasinghe 2024).",
    "The combination of human olfactory receptors with AI-based pattern recognition models has further advanced the accuracy and reliability of these systems, enabling precise odor reproduction and manipulation.",
    "Recent developments in personalized AI models have introduced a new dimension to olfactory data analysis, making it possible to tailor AI systems to individual sensory experiences."
  ]
}